==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Koodoo
<hw>Koo"doo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large South African antelope (<spn>Strepsiceros kudu</spn>). The males
have graceful spiral horns, sometimes four feet long. The general color
is reddish or grayish brown, with eight or nine white bands on each
side, and a pale dorsal stripe. The old males become dark bluish gray,
due to the skin showing through the hair. The females are hornless.
Called also <altname>nellut</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kudu</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kookoom</ent>⟦br⟧
